name: Bin Fan
message:
Fix IndexOutOfBoundsException on async cache

### What changes are proposed in this pull request?

Fix https://github.com/Alluxio/alluxio/issues/13828 and fix
https://github.com/Alluxio/alluxio/issues/13050

This patch will fix a miscaculation of block to async cache

In earlier Alluxio versions prior to
https://github.com/Alluxio/alluxio/pull/13064, users may see the
following errors:
```
2021-03-12 08:36:48,521 ERROR AlluxioFuseFileSystem - Failed to read
file=/data/0.5G_9.txt, offset=536862720, size=8192
java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException: Index: 4, Size: 4
```

After 13064, we will not see the error anymore but caching the last
block when fileSize happens on block size boundary will fail silently.

### Why are the changes needed?

Correct a bug when calculating the block id to async cache, when current
pos is fileSize which is a multiple of blockSize

### Does this PR introduce any user facing changes?

No

name: Zhan Yuan
message:
Add CacheContext to URIStatus to enable per-read metrics

Add functions to URIStatus to track bytes read from cache and external
file system in a per-read basis.
The default implementation does nothing. It is up to the subclass to
decide how to track them.
Presto will use this information to compute query level metrics.
See https://github.com/prestodb/presto/issues/16237 for details.

There are no user facing changes in this commit.

Make CommandMessageFilter implementations Jackson serializable

Adjust all the CommandMessageFilter implementations to be
de-/serializable through the JacksonSerializer. As such it would be
beneficial to provide distinct parameterized serialization test cases
for all implementations, going over the set of available serializers.
This will likely adjust all CommandMessageFilter impls to contain JSON
specific annotations.

name: Steven van Beelen
message:
Adjust SnapshotFilter API

Change the SnapshotFilter API to be more to the point. In doing so,
rename `filter` to `allow`, as the function should allow or reject
snapshot data. On top, only the `and` operation is used, which logically
 should be `combine`, as you'd combine these allow methods, not "and"
 them.

#1391

name: Allard Buijze
message:
Added support for annotated handler interceptors

This commit adds support for interceptors declared on the handler
instance itself, using the same rules for parameter injection as other
annotated handlers. Depending on the annotation used, handlers are also
given the opportunity to only act on the result of handler execution,
such as a specific type of exception.

Resolves #901

name: Steve Loughran
message:
HADOOP-16207 Improved S3A MR tests.

Contributed by Steve Loughran.

Replaces the committer-specific terasort and MR test jobs with parameterization
of the (now single tests) and use of file:// over hdfs:// as the cluster FS.

The parameterization ensures that only one of the specific committer tests
run at a time -overloads of the test machines are less likely, and so the
suites can be pulled back into the parallel phase.

There's also more detailed validation of the stage outputs of the terasorting;
if one test fails the rest are all skipped. This and the fact that job
output is stored under target/yarn-${timestamp} means failures should
be more debuggable.

Change-Id: Iefa370ba73c6419496e6e69dd6673d00f37ff095
